@node "9_1" "r7-c (10.01.2013)"
@{fg fill}@{u}9.1. r7-c (10.01.2013)@{uu}@{fg text}
* @{b}Really@{ub} fixed WHLoad games not working when they use "kick34005.A500".  AmigaOS4.1 Update 5 must have been installed first.

@endnode

@node "9_2" "r7-b (26-08-2012)"
@{fg fill}@{u}9.2. r7-b (26-08-2012)@{uu}@{fg text}
* Fixed WHLoad games not working when they use "kick34005.A500".  AmigaOS4.1 Update 5 must have been installed first.  Thanks to Joel Edberg for reporting the bug.
* Slightly improved how the installer asks for a Workbench3.1 folder to be created in Advanced mode, thanks to a suggestion by Philippe Ferrucci.

@endnode

@node "9_3" "r7 (15-08-2012)"
@{fg fill}@{u}9.3. r7 (15-08-2012)@{uu}@{fg text}
* Stopped the installer adding 320x256/etc screenmodes to RadeonHD cards, as they caused E-UAE's screen to not be visible.
* For RadeonHD users, the installer now (offers to) remove 320x256/etc screenmodes (see above).
* Now defaults to 640x480 for RadeonHD cards, so E-UAE will be full-screen on the X1000, etc.
* For RadeonHD cards, 640x480 uses a frame skip of 0 (instead of 1). So the X1000 & Sam460 should have smoother emulation.

* Per-game settings are now MUCH easier to understand & use, thanks to heavily reworking the menus & changing the main window's behaviour.
* E-UAE can now be run in windowed mode (rather than full-screen), due to user demand (but beware it is not suitable for anything that uses the mouse).
* Added menu option to use E-UAE-amigfx's built-in floppy drive noise emulation, and also fixed the disabling of floppy drive noises not working!
* Added menu option for starting RunInUAE hidden, so users don't need to fiddle with the CX_POPUP tooltype.

* E-UAE's own file requester for game disks (Ctrl-Alt-F1/etc) now shows the current ADF folder, thanks to a suggestion from Philippe Ferrucci.
* Added Libs & Fonts work-around for games that have not been properly installed to Workbench3.1 (e.g. some GRAC-based games).  Does not work with a fake Workbench 3.1.
* Updated WHDLoad from v16.9 to v17.0, for better compatibility with recent WHDLoad slaves.
* Now handles problematic volume names that would break the emulated Workbench 3.x (and removes bad volume names that have already been added).  Thanks to Sicky for reporting his RunInUAE problems.

* Fixed WHDLoad games launched from the Shell not working, such as iGame does.  So iGame works again!  Thanks to Cass for reporting the bug.
* Fixed 68k scripts with spaces in their name not working.
* Fixed HD games with per-game settings not starting correctly (or at all), if WB3.1's location was changed during installation.
* Fixed HD games with per-game settings having the wrong WB screen mode, if the user subsequently changed the default screen size.
* The "SaveGames" disk is no-longer missing when creating a per-game config file for a HD installed game.  Thanks to DAX for reporting the bug.
* Fixed 'Set * to > default' menu items crashing RunInUAE.  Surprised that no-one reported this r4 bug :( .
* Fixed ticked menu items (like "Basic Workbench mode") sometimes getting the wrong state after being used.

* The UNinstaller now asks about deleting your Workbench3.1 & E-UAE folders.
* The installer & UNinstaller icons now use the Execute command instead of the Script flag, due to them otherwise not working for too many people (who don't use UnArc & thus the Script flag was not preserved).
* The installer was setting certain RunInUAE settings back to their defaults (default joystick, default screen size, floppy drive noises, Leave Workbench prefs alone, E-UAE stay in background, icon tooltypes).
* The installer could forget where E-UAE was installed if it was cancelled.  It could also think your recent choices were where RunInUAE/etc was last installed.
* The installer could wrongly add a new RunInUAE icon to AmiDock if the previous installation used Simple Mode & the current one did not (or vice versa).
* The installer now closes & restarts RunInUAE, if it was already running.
* The installer no-longer deletes the E-UAE-amigfx folder when replacing it.  Thanks to Scott Cabit for reporting the potential problem.
* The installer now offers to move your old E-UAE folder, when you choose a new installation location.  This avoids the confusion of two folders, and helps retain any existing ROMs & settings.
* The installer now creates restore points, if AmiSystemRestore is installed.

* Added the "Debug_Backup" program, to help me debug any problems people have.
* Executable sizes have been reduced by 60-120KB, thanks to an OS4 SDK discovery made by Kas1e.
* Now handles all menu actions, rather than just the last one.  Thanks to prodding from Scott Cabit!
* The stability of Workbench patches may be improved, thanks to indirect improvements made for AmiSystemRestore.  (Although I had not noticed any problems.)
* Now shows the game name instead of "WHDLoad" for WHDLoad games launched from the Shell, such as iGame does.
* Now allows per-game settings to manually specify that Basic Workbench mode is prefered, by adding the line #RUNINUAE: WORKBENCHMODE=BASIC
* Now ignores (manually added) filesystem2 lines in the .uaerc file, since that is what E-UAE does.  Thanks to Mehdi Boulahia for reporting symptoms of this bug.
* Removed the unnecessary message "The program X is not visible inside E-UAE.  So updating E-UAE's config file...".
* No-longer asks for permission to create a per-game config file, as this worried at least one user that it was a bad thing to do!

@endnode

@node "9_4" "r6 (16-12-2011)"
@{fg fill}@{u}9.4. r6 (16-12-2011)@{uu}@{fg text}
* RunInUAE is now part of AmigaOS4.1 Update 4, as a Contribution :-)
* Added support for the emulation files that come with AmigaOS4.1 Update 4, so an Amiga Forever CD is not needed in that case.
* Improved CD32 & CDTV compatibility.  (Fears & Whales Voyage now start.)
* Enabled CD32 Non-Volatile RAM support, so saved games are no-longer lost.  Thanks to help from Michael Trebilcock.
* Added a "SaveGames" floppy disk for HD installed games.
* Now uses Ringhio for game-launch notifications, if possible.
* Now warns the user if their default screen mode will not be full-screen.
* Fixed non-AmigaForever Kickstarts being wrongly rejected as not compatible with WHDLoad.
* Fixed 320x240 & 320x256 screenmodes not being added, even though DDC had never been enabled.
* Fixed 320x240 & 320x256 screenmodes no-longer working with AmigaOS4.1 Update 3, but please make sure you add them again if asked during installation.
* Fixing of corrupt per-game config files didn't work.  Now fixed.
* Fixed excessive memory use & crash from lack of memory, especially during installation, which arose from a PortablE bug.
* Fixed failure to create an ARexx port (and possible crash) in certain circumstances.
* Now uses the latest (30th July 2011) release of E-UAE-amigfx.  E-UAE must be re-installed to use this version.
* Cleaned-up the installer & fixed some bugs in the process.  Replaced DoIcon with my own simple clone.
* Added an UNinstaller for RunInUAE.
* Improved documentation, especially regarding DiskImage.

@endnode

@node "9_5" "r5 (14-07-2011)"
@{fg fill}@{u}9.5. r5 (14-07-2011)@{uu}@{fg text}
* If you don't have an Amiga Forever CD, you no-longer have to supply files from a Workbench 3.1 disk (as a suitable fake WB3.1 will be created - although compatibility is lower).
* Fixed an r4 installation bug where RunInUAE might not run right automatically until it had been run once manually.  Many thanks to DAX for reporting this bug.
* Changed E-UAE's priority from -1 to 0, to improve emulation performance.  Thanks to DAX for his suggestion.
* Various tweaks to E-UAE's configuration to improve emulation compatibility, accuracy & performance.  Heavily based upon DAX's suggestions.
* The installer will create the "kick34005.A500" & (with the AF 2008+ CD) "kick40068.A1200" files, which are needed by some WHDLoad games (such as Lucas Arts adventures).  Thanks to DAX for help.
* Improved patching of Workbench, to hopefully work on all versions of AmigaOS4, including Update 3 for AmigaOS4.1.  Thanks to Colin Wenzel for his help, and Philippe Ferrucci for testing.
* Added support for DMS disk images.  Also the Insert disk requester now only shows files of the right type.
* Added option to not change Workbench 3.1's screenmode prefs.  Requested by Philippe Ferrucci.
* Add a Help menu item, and the main window also reacts to the Help key.  Added after many requests for this!
* Would wrongly open an empty Notepad when answering No to creating a per-game config file.
* When using a pre-existing Workbench 3.1 installation, it now ensures that the correct WbRun command is installed.  Thanks to Philippe Ferrucci for reporting this bug.
* Added Mason's pretty icons for RunInUAE's folder, plus UAE's folder & program.  Thanks to DAX for pointing them out.
* The installer's "Select ROM" file requester now starts in E-UAE's folder, for convenience.  Thanks to Philippe Ferrucci for suggesting this.

@endnode

@node "9_6" "r4 (11-03-2011)"
@{fg fill}@{u}9.6. r4 (11-03-2011)@{uu}@{fg text}
* Added a CD32 emulation option!  Use the "Boot CD32 from" item from the "Control E-UAE" menu.
* E-UAE's Workbench now uses a High-Res screen mode when a 640x480 screen is used.  Much nicer, especially for programs!

* Stopped an occasional RunInUAE start-up crash, which could happen when patching Workbench.
* Removed the "640x480 (for programs)" menu option, as it was unnecessary.
* Strips the path from WHDLoad & IconX default tooltypes, so now more likely to work inside E-UAE.

* The installer now avoids adding 320x240/etc screenmodes for those using DDC, since this sadly has unpredictable effects on Workbench & other screens. (Addendum: With r6 this has been removed for user of Update 4.)
* Removed need for the C:RunInUAE_dummy executable.  It will be deleted by the installer if it exists.
* Rewrote the menu code, which makes it far easier to modify, and also looks a bit better.

@endnode

@node "9_7" "r3 (02-04-2010)"
@{fg fill}@{u}9.7. r3 (02-04-2010)@{uu}@{fg text}
* Now patches Workbench to allow double-clicked 68k programs & scripts to be run inside E-UAE!
* Now supports AGA for ADF games.
* Collisions should now work for HD installed games.
* Added emulation of floppy drive noises!  Not as accurate as WinUAE's, but good enough.
* Made it a commodity, with menus & an optional AppIcon.
* E-UAE's verbose output is now hidden, but available if you need it.
* The Settings menu means you no-longer need to directly edit the RunInUAE.cfg file.
* The "Control E-UAE" menu allows direct control of E-UAE.  And frame skip can be stored for each game.
* You no-longer need to reset E-UAE before running another HD installed game.  This greatly simplifies the usage of RunInUAE.
* You can choose to use a 640x480 screen mode, if you monitor doesn't support 320x240 or 320x256.

* Automated virtually all of the manual installation steps.
* Worked-around an AmigaOS4.1 Update 1 bug, so the installer works again.  And fixed many bugs in the installer.
* The installer now offers to use your previous installation choices.
* New users have the option of a Simple installation mode.
* Comes with E-UAE amigfx v0.8.29, which is by far the best version (fast but no crashes).

* Added a Basic Workbench mode for anyone who has trouble starting HD installed games.  This also provides faster booting of E-UAE.
* Doubled the default time out (to 20 seconds) before giving-up on E-UAE responding.
* Now allows launching of programs from the Ram Disk.
* Now works with iGame/etc, which start WHDLoad from the Shell.
* Now removes virtual volumes with obsolete paths.  Useful for HDF games.
* Now sets the stack size, to prevent E-UAE crashing when started by double-clicking a WHDLoad game.
* Fixed parsing of pre-existing "filesystem=" lines in the E-UAE config file.  Should prevent duplicate entries being created.
* Ensures the OS3.x User-Startup has one (and only one) uae_rcli line.
* Various other small changes & improvements!

@endnode

@node "9_8" "r2 (03-01-2010)"
@{fg fill}@{u}9.8. r2 (03-01-2010)@{uu}@{fg text}
* Now opens a small App Window for you to drop games on.  Easier than dropping them on AmiDock!
* Now automatically identifies & loads multi-disk games, due to user demand.
* Has a new icon thanks to David Braconnier.
* Bug fix: Installation of the WHDLoad.key could stop Workbench 3.x from starting, if the user did not actually click on the key file.
* Bug fix: Per-drawer & per-game config files stopped RunInUAE from working when E-UAE was not already running.  Bug reported by Amigo1.
* Bug fix: Per-drawer & per-game config files were never used for ADFs.
* The name of the HD installed game being launched is now shown inside E-UAE.
* An improved installer & manual, thanks to user feedback.

@endnode

@node "9_9" "r1 (24-12-2009)"
@{fg fill}@{u}9.9. r1 (24-12-2009)@{uu}@{fg text}
* The first public release! 
@endnode
